ames]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2015 Southeast Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Competitors at the 2017 Southeast Asian Games]]\n[[Category:Universiade bronze medalists for Malaysia]]\n\n{{Malaysia-sport-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Malaysian diver}}\n{{EngvarB|date=September 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2014}}\n{{Infobox sportsperson\n|name= Leong Mun Yee\n|image=Leong Mun Yee 2010.jpg\n|caption = Leong at the 2010 Commonwealth Games\n|nationality= Malayisan\n|birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|12|4|df=y}}\n|birth_place = [[Ipoh]], [[Perak]], [[Malaysia]]<ref name=sr>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/le/leong-mun-yee-1.html Leong Mun Yee]. Sports Reference profile</ref>\n|height= 1.63 m\n|weight= 55 kg\n|country= Malaysia\n|sport=[[Diving (sport)|Diving]]\n|event= 1&nbsp;m, 3&nbsp;m, 3&nbsp;m synchro, 10&nbsp;m, 10&nbsp;m synchro\n|partner= [[Pandelela Rinong]]\n\n|show-medals = no\n|medaltemplates= \n{{MedalCompetition|[[FINA World Aquatics Championships|World Championships]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2019 World Aquatics Championships|2019 Gwangju]]|[[Diving at the 2019 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Women's synchronized 10 metre platform|10 m synchro]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[Diving at the 2009 World Aquatics Championships|2009 Rome]]|[[Diving at the 2009 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Women's synchronized 10 metre platform|10 m synchro]]}}\n{{MedalBronze|[[Diving at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships|2013 Barcelona]]|[[Diving at the 2013 World Aquatics Championships \u2013 Women's synchronized 10 metre platform|10 m synchro]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[FINA Diving World Series|World Series]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[2011 FINA Diving World Series|2011 Beijing]]|[[2011 FINA Diving World Series|10 m synchro]]}}\n{{MedalCompetition|[[Diving at the Asian Games|Asian Games]]}}\n{{MedalSilver|[[Diving at the 2010 Asian Games|2010 Guangzhou]]|[[Diving at the 2010 Asian Games \u2013 Women's synchronized 3 metre springboard|3 m sy